explains: adj. 东南方的；朝东南的

sentences.en: On Christmas Eve in 1994, humans entered a cave in the mountains of southeastern France for what was probably the first time in 20,000 years.
sentences.cn: 1994年圣诞前夜，人类进入了法国东南部山区的一个洞穴，这可能是2万年来的第一次。

sentences.en: Research now indicates that sizable areas of southeastern Alaska along the inner continental shelf were not covered by ice toward the end of the last Ice Age.
sentences.cn: 现在的研究表明，阿拉斯加东南部沿着内大陆架的相当大的区域在最后一个冰河时代末期并没有被冰覆盖。

sentences.en: This phenomenon was not necessarily confined to the Pleistocene, but may have occurred much earlier in the Southeastern Asian islands, although evidence is fragmentary.
sentences.cn: 尽管证据很少，但这种现象并不一定局限于更新世，而可能在东南亚诸岛发生得更早。
